      "<b>Part 3: Debating the Importance of Addressing These Issues</b>:<br><br>Preparation for Debate:<br>Explain the rules of a debate: each group will represent one side of the argument, either for or against the importance of addressing the issue they’ve been assigned.<br>Provide students with key points they can use in their debate:<br>Health: 'Why is health important for everyone?' and 'How can we improve health awareness?'<br>Gender-Based Violence: 'How can we reduce gender-based violence?' and 'Why should we ensure gender equality?'<br>HIV/AIDS: 'What are the ways to prevent HIV?' and 'Why should we support people living with HIV?'<br>Child Abuse: 'What are the effects of child abuse?' and 'How can we protect children?'<br>Debate Format:<br>Assign each group to take turns presenting their arguments in favor of addressing their issue. After each presentation, allow the opposing side to ask questions or present counterarguments. Conclude the debate with a class discussion on why all these issues should be addressed for the betterment of society.",
