      "<b>Part 5: Exercise: Create Awareness Campaigns</b>:<br><br>Task: Now that students have learned about these issues and debated their importance, they will work in groups to create a campaign for raising awareness about one of the issues discussed.<br>Instructions:<br>Choose one issue (health, gender-based violence, HIV/AIDS, or child abuse).<br>Create a poster, slogan, or short skit that educates others on the importance of addressing the issue and how people can help.<br>Encourage creativity and make the campaigns as engaging as possible, using visuals, slogans, and clear messages.<br>Class Presentation: Each group will present their campaign to the class, explaining the message they are promoting and how it can help raise awareness about the chosen issue."
