      "<b>Part 2: Introduction to 'Imiti ikula empanga'</b>:<br><br>Teach the meaning of the Bemba proverb, 'Imiti ikula empanga,' which translates to 'The trees grow in the forest.' The proverb means that growth or progress happens in the right environment. Just as trees need the forest to grow, people need the right surroundings and opportunities to develop and succeed.<br><br>Context: Explain how this saying is used to encourage making wise choices about one's environment and associations. Discuss real-life applications, such as how family, friends, school, or community can influence personal growth and success.",
      "<b>Part 3: Importance of Proverbs in Daily Life</b>:<br><br>Help students understand how proverbs guide behavior and decision-making. Ask students to reflect on proverbs they know and share their meanings. Discuss how proverbs can be applied in their own lives.<br><br>Group Discussion: Lead a discussion on the importance of choosing a good environment for growth. Discuss how where you live, who you associate with, and your community can influence your development.",
